#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:486
msgid "Common placement settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:488
msgid "Some label placement settings are available for all layer geometry types:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:491
msgid "Data Defined"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:493
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Data Defined` group provides direct control on labels "
"placement, on a feature-by-feature basis. It relies on their attributes "
"or an expression to set:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:497
msgid "the :guilabel:`X` and :guilabel:`Y` coordinate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:498
msgid "the text alignment over the custom position set above:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:500
msgid ":guilabel:`Horizontal`: it can be **Left**, **Center** or **Right**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:501
msgid ""
"the text :guilabel:`Vertical`: it can be **Bottom**, **Base**, **Half**, "
"**Cap** or **Top**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:503
msgid ""
"the text :guilabel:`Rotation`. Check the :guilabel:`Preserve data "
"rotation values` entry if you want to keep the rotation value in the "
"associated field and apply it to the label, whether the label is pinned "
"or not. If unchecked, unpinning the label rotation is reset and its value"
" cleared from the attribute table."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:509
msgid ""
"Data-defined rotation with polygon features is currently supported only "
"with the :guilabel:`Around centroid` placement mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:512
msgid ""
"Expressions can not be used in combination with the labels map tools (ie "
"the :guilabel:`Rotate label` and :guilabel:`Move label` tools) to :ref"
":`data-define <data_defined>` labels placement. The widget will be reset "
"to the corresponding :ref:`auxiliary storage field "
"<vector_auxiliary_storage>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:521
msgid "Priority"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:523
msgid ""
"In the :guilabel:`Priority` section you can define the placement priority"
" rank of each label, ie if there are different diagrams or labels "
"candidates for the same location, the item with the higher priority will "
"be displayed and the others could be left out."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:528
msgid ""
"The priority rank is also used to evaluate whether a label could be "
"omitted due to a greater weighted :ref:`obstacle feature "
"<labels_obstacles>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:534
msgid "Obstacles"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:536
msgid ""
"In some contexts (eg, high density labels, overlapping features...), the "
"labels placement can result in labels being placed over unrelated "
"features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:539
msgid ""
"An obstacle is a feature over which QGIS avoids placing other features' "
"labels or diagrams. This can be controlled from the :guilabel:`Obstacles`"
" section:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:542
msgid ""
"Activate the |checkbox| :guilabel:`Discourage labels and diagrams from "
"covering features` option to decide whether features of the layer should "
"act as obstacles for any label and diagram (including items from other "
"features in the same layer)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:546
msgid ""
"Instead of the whole layer, you can select a subset of features to use as"
" obstacles, using the |dataDefined| :sup:`data-defined override` control "
"next to the option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:550
msgid "Use the :guilabel:`Settings` button to tweak the obstacle's weighting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:552
msgid ""
"For every potential obstacle feature you can assign an "
":guilabel:`Obstacle weight`: any :ref:`label <labels_priority>` or "
":ref:`diagram <diagram_placement>` whose placement priority rank is "
"greater than this value can be placed over. Labels or diagrams with lower"
" rank will be omitted if no other placement is possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:558
msgid ""
"This weighting can also be data-defined, so that within the same layer, "
"certain features are more likely to be covered than others."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:560
msgid "For polygon layers, you can choose the kind of obstacle the feature is:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:562
msgid ""
"**over the feature's interior**: avoids placing labels over the interior "
"of the polygon (prefers placing labels totally outside or just slightly "
"inside the polygon)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:565
msgid ""
"or **over the feature's boundary**: avoids placing labels over the "
"boundary of the polygon (prefers placing labels outside or completely "
"inside the polygon). This can be useful for layers where the features "
"cover the whole area (administrative units, categorical coverages, ...). "
"In this case, it is impossible to avoid placing labels within these "
"features, and it looks much better when placing them over the boundaries "
"between features is avoided."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:577
msgid "Rendering tab"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:579
msgid ""
"In the |render| :guilabel:`Rendering` tab, you can tune when the labels "
"can be rendered and their interaction with other labels and features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:583
msgid "Label options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:585
msgid "Under :guilabel:`Label options`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:587
msgid ""
"You find the :ref:`scale-based <label_scaledepend>` and the "
":guilabel:`Pixel size-based` visibility settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:590
msgid ""
"The :guilabel:`Label z-index` determines the order in which labels are "
"rendered, as well in relation with other feature labels in the layer "
"(using data-defined override expression), as with labels from other "
"layers. Labels with a higher z-index are rendered on top of labels (from "
"any layer) with lower z-index."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:595
msgid ""
"Additionally, the logic has been tweaked so that if two labels have "
"matching z-indexes, then:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:598
msgid ""
"if they are from the same layer, the smaller label will be drawn above "
"the larger label"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:600
msgid ""
"if they are from different layers, the labels will be drawn in the same "
"order as their layers themselves (ie respecting the order set in the map "
"legend)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:603
msgid ""
"This setting doesn't make labels to be drawn below the features from "
"other layers, it just controls the order in which labels are drawn on top"
" of all the layers' features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:607
msgid ""
"While rendering labels and in order to display readable labels, QGIS "
"automatically evaluates the position of the labels and can hide some of "
"them in case of collision. You can however choose to |checkbox| "
":guilabel:`Show all labels for this layer (including colliding labels)` "
"in order to manually fix their placement (see :ref:`label_toolbar`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:612
msgid ""
"With data-defined expressions in :guilabel:`Show label` and "
":guilabel:`Always Show` you can fine tune which labels should be "
"rendered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:614
msgid ""
"Allow to :guilabel:`Show upside-down labels`: alternatives are **Never**,"
" **when rotation defined** or **always**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:618
msgid "Feature options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:620
msgid "Under :guilabel:`Feature options`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:622
msgid ""
"You can choose to :guilabel:`label every part of a multi-part feature` "
"and :guilabel:`limit the number of features to be labeled`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:624
msgid ""
"Both line and polygon layers offer the option to set a minimum size for "
"the features to be labeled, using :guilabel:`Suppress labeling of "
"features smaller than`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:627
msgid ""
"For polygon features, you can also filter the labels to show according to"
" whether they completely fit within their feature or not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../docs/user_manual/style_library/label_settings.rst:629
msgid ""
"For line features, you can choose to :guilabel:`Merge connected lines to "
"avoid duplicate labels`, rendering a quite airy map in conjunction with "
"the :guilabel:`Distance` or :guilabel:`Repeat` options in the "
":ref:`Placement <labels_line_placement>` tab."
msgstr ""

